                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rockaut",
                        "name": "rockaut",
                        "displayName": "Markus",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Seems to work for me!\nBut i have to mention, that there is another problem with session (Zend_Application_Resource_Session) since 1.8.1 so i don't know if it works in my normal usage -- currently i have a workaround for session management.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rockaut",
                        "name": "rockaut",
                        "displayName": "Markus",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-16T06:21:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-16T06:21:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31235",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi\n\nwhy you do not only use the php function \"sys_get_temp_dir\" and why you check if it exists ?\nThe function is available since php 5.2.1 and zend framework version is 5.2.4\n-> http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/requirements.html#requirements.version\n\nAnd if the systems temp dir is not writable this is a wrong configured (or crashed) system",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-21T15:27:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-21T15:27:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31244",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The method I referred to in the second issue does use this method additionally.\nBUT: You can not only refer to this method alone as it is possible that this method does not return correct informations. This is due OS dependency. Therefor additional checks are also provided which make sure that the path can be detected even if sys_* does not work properly.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-21T23:56:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-21T23:56:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31252",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Are you sure? I could not find where the problem occurs ?\nAnd why it have to check first if the function exists ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
